item.description:
@bakatool wrote:

    try {
        body-code
    } catch (exception-classname variable-name) {
        handler-code
    }

try/catch is used if your server has a error it would handle the error without CRashing your whole server… if you open a TRY you gotta close it with a catch.

like if you open a IF statment

if(SOMETHING

you gotta close it with a )

if(SOMETHING)

basically…

your CUSTOMCOMMAND method is alllllllllllllllllllllllllllll inside a big try {…

but the catch was removed

if your YELL Command is the last command for that method You can catch it at the end
